<body>
Reports a method call to <code>document.write()</code> or <code>document.writeln()</code>.
Most usages of such calls are performed better with explicit
DOM calls, such as <code>getElementByID()</code> and
<code>createElement()</code>.  Additionally, the <code>write()</code> and
<code>writeln()</code> calls will not work with XML
DOMs, including DOMs for XHTML if viewed as XML.  This can result in difficulty to point out bugs.
